BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (19): BULGARIA, PORTUGAL
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[The need for complementary data on recently reported bluetongue-affected
Bulgaria and Portugal has been raised in ProMED-mail postings 20061106.3191
and 20061111.3238, respectively. Some hitherto unpublished information from
both countries has become available from their presentations during the
last meeting of EU's Standing Committee on the Food Chain and Animal Health
(SCFCAH), held in Brussels on 8 Nov 2006. The above, as well as
presentations from other 5 member countries, are available under the title
"Bluetongue outbreaks in the northern part of the EU" at
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/controlmeasures/bluetongue_outbreaks_en.htm>.
The following transcribed data have been derived from the presentations of
Bulgaria and Portugal. Readers are encouraged to see the other
presentations at the above URL. - Mod.AS]
[1] Portugal
[2] Bulgaria
