[1] Portugal
Date: 12 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: EU Health & Consumer Protection DG web-site [edited]
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/bluetongue_portugal08112006.pdf>

Control Measures For Bluetongue - Portugal 2006
-----------------------------------------------
30 Sep 2006: Detection of 7 PCR-positives (pooled sampling) in a bovine
sentinel holding at Vila Franca de Xira, within the Council of Azambuja (in
the free zone, contiguous with the restricted area). [For location, see
maps in slides 21, 22, 23].
12 Oct 2006: All 20 animals in the above holding individually tested with
negative PCR results. [The contradiction between the PCR results in both
testings deserves explanation].
Following the detection of the seropositive cattle in Vila Franca de Xira,
the following measures have been taken:
1. Testing of all animals for individual Elisa and RT-PCR.
2. Movement restrictions within a 20-km radius.
3. Surveillance activities (clinical, serological, entomological) within
the said 20-km radius.
Results of the serological surveillance in the 20-km radius:
- Holdings: From 837 bovine holdings, 107 were tested, of which 64 were
ELISA positive (59.81 percent), and 4 were PCR positive (6.25 percent).
- Animals: from 24 782 bovine animals, 677 were tested, of which 226 were
ELISA positive (33.38 percent), and 24 were PCR positive (3.55 percent).
- New PCR positive results detected in Vila Franca de Xira.
Consequent steps:
- Enlargement of the restricted area
- Vaccination of ovines
The presentation includes maps of the restricted areas and free zone. The
restricted areas are south of latitude 40. The following geographical
regions are included in the restricted areas:
Region 4 = Beira Interior (about 50 percent of surface, southern part);
Region 5 = Ribatejo e Oeste (about 50 percent of surface, southern part);
Region 6 = Alentejo (entire region);
Region 7 = Algarve (entire region).
The presentation includes also the following information on BTV vaccination
schemes carried out, so far, in Portugal:
1. Ovines
- In the protection zone, 2 Feb 2005 - 9 May 2005:
Live vaccine of serotype 4 (South Africa) was applied. Execution rate = 97
percent of animals in the zone.
- In the surveillance zone, 10 Nov 2005 - 24 Jan 2006: Inactivated vaccine
serotype 4 was applied. Execution rate = 98 percent.
- In the ex-protection zone, 7 Feb 2006 - 9 May 2006: Live vaccine of
serotype 4 (South Africa) was applied. Execution rate: 85 percent of
holdings, 87 percent of animals [see table 1 in slide 16 for the detailed
figures for each region].
Vaccination campaign in bovines (Inactivated vaccine):
1. Field trial of inactivated vaccine (serotypes 2 and 4), August - October
2005: About 4000 bovines vaccinated in the Region of Alentejo.
2. Serotype 4, December 2005 until July 2006: Low demand (no vector activity).
3. Serotype 4, July 2006 - September 2006. Fattening animals sent to the
free zone; final destiny: Slaughter within Portugal (vaccination registered
on the animal passports). Primary vaccination: Minimal age 3 months; 2
inoculations with 21-day interval and movement between 30 and 180 days
after 1st inoculation.
Total number vaccinated - 42 000 bovines (for data from each region, see
table in slide 17).
--
